<p class="article-lead">Crimp and screw perfume pumps solve the same closure problem with different assembly, appearance
    and rework characteristics.</p>
<h2>Crimp pumps</h2>
<p>A crimped ferrule creates the classic sealed perfume finish and is difficult to open without damage. It requires
    matching neck dimensions, controlled crimp settings and inspection for deformation or leakage.</p>
<h2>Screw pumps</h2>
<p>A threaded closure can simplify assembly and replacement, but torque, thread fit and tamper expectations must be
    managed. The visible collar and cap geometry may differ.</p>
<p>Neither is automatically superior. Choose after considering bottle availability, filling equipment, intended
    appearance, transport testing and whether the pack needs to be reopened. Test the exact bottle, pump, gasket and liquid
    combination.</p>